description:
The fraction three quarters has a particular interest to biologists because of its link to the research of Max Kleiber and metabolic rates in animals.
More links & stuff in full description below âââ

This video features Thomas Woolley from the University of Oxford.

Tom thanks @gameboygenius for pointing out the following: Small mistake. I think where you said they expected MR â r^(2/3) you actually meant to say MR â m^(2/3). If you take the r/V/A relations and solve for A, you get A â V^(2/3). Mass is proportional to volume, so roughly  A â m^(2/3). If we then assume MR is proportional to area, the final assumption would be MR â m^(2/3)."
